result.execSummary:
All charges against Michael P Gallagher in this case have been dismissed. These charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Michael P Gallagher is presumed innocent.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Michael P Gallagher not in court.  Attorney Karl Peter Hayes in court for State of Wisconsin. State notes defendant has been extradited to Illinois.  Court dismisses on own motion.

1:23 PM Defendant Michael P Gallagher appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Karl Peter Hayes in court for State of Wisconsin. Defendant has not received criminal complaint.  State will email to the jail for service on defendant.  Court finds probable cause.  Defendant needs to review waiver of extradition.  Defendant received complaint during hearing.  Court allows time for defendant to review complaint.  Defendant waives right to extradition.  Rights given.  Court finds defendant is making a knowing and voluntary waiver of right to extradition, and Illinois will be able to secure return.  Defendant's custody remanded to the Vilas County Sheriff pending return to the State of Illinois
Status hearing scheduled for June 20, 2022 at 10:15 am.
